    <title>Configure DHIS2 programs to work on Android apps</title>
    <para>To use event programs and tracker programs on the Android Event Capture and Tracker
        Capture apps, you must configure the programs in DHIS2.</para>
    <orderedlist>
        <listitem>
            <para>Create a user with the correct settings:</para>
            <orderedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para>In DHIS2 web, create a user.</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Assign a user role ...</para>
                    <?oxy_custom_start type="oxy_content_highlight" color="235,192,230"?>
                    <para>You need to: assign a user role that allow user to access programs</para>
                    <?oxy_custom_end?>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Assign programs to the user role.</para>
                    <?oxy_custom_start type="oxy_content_highlight" color="235,192,230"?>
                    <para>User role must have programs assigned to it.</para>
                    <?oxy_custom_end?>
                </listitem>
            </orderedlist>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Configure the program: </para>
            <para>Open the <emphasis role="bold">Program</emphasis> app and ...Assign program to
                organisation units. Select the organisation unit(s) you </para>
            <note>
                <para>To work on Andorid: same data capture and maintenance organisation unit as the
                    organisation unit the program is assigned to.</para>
            </note>
            <note>
                <para>Important to only select the actual data capture organisation unit, if you
                    select top organisation unit, the Event Tracker and the Tracker Capture Android
                    apps, download ALL data for the organisation unit. </para>
            </note>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Open an Andorid app and log in with the user you created.</para>
            <para>Now: download programs and organisation units (everything the user has acces
                to).</para>
            <para>Pull down to synch with DHIS2
                <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20161102T151130+0100" comment="Add screen shot."?>web<?oxy_comment_end?>.</para>
        </listitem>
    </orderedlist>
